s pernicious system along with essays that outline a set of practical guides to its radical reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aLabor History. 4aSociology & Social Science.  afactory, supply chains, world trade, workers, manufacturers, export industries, global South.1 aAppelbaum, Richard P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLichtenstein, Nelson, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170335540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501703355423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501703355/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles